$ SAS programming, function putn
@ putn

`putn` allows to convert a numeric value to a character value with a *dynamic format*. In contrast, the → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/formats-informats[format] of the
→ Companies-Products/SAS/programming/functions/put[put statement] must be specified at compile time.

